title: For Sale:  Detonics Combat Master Mk I. .45 ACP
postcontent:
WTS a Detonics Combat Master Mk I. .45 ACP.

This is one of the original Seattle, Washington guns -- mfg in 1976 or 77, one of the first 1000 Detonics pistols built. I purchased this from the original owner in Seattle.

As you can see, the gun has a later style blued slide, barrel, and hammer, as well as the later factory checkered wood grips. The original owner explained that the gun originally shot low and left, so after fiddling with it for several years he eventually took it back to Detonics in the 1980s and had them fix it. The result was the gun's current configuration. It still has the original rubber-backed mainspring housing.

Gun is in excellent condition with just the slightest bit of finish wear on the corners. Overall 90+% condition, this gun has been a safe queen with both the previous owner and me. Gun functions perfectly and shoots accurately.

Comes with holster Bianchi #7L (right-handed) and original Detonics soft case/rug and one original Detonics magazine.

The PF-9 has been customized: polished magazine release, take-down pin, and slide catch, mirror polished feed ramp, and painted front sights. This gun has never been shot. I am only selling it because after buying it, I found that it really doesn't fit my hands to my liking. Comes with a Yaqui style belt holster (pictured). Includes everything that came with it new, and one magazine. The PF-9 retains the best features from our P-11 and P-3AT pistols combined into the flattest and lightest single stack 9mm configuration ever made. The barrel, locking system, slide stop, assembly pin, front sight, recoil springs and guide rod are adapted from the P-11. The PF-9 is nearly identical to the P-11 in length and height and shares the same exterior controls. The shorter trigger system with integral hammer block and the extraction system are adapted from the P-3AT. Just like the P-11, the PF-9 will accept +P ammunition, however, not with continuous use. The rear sight is a new design and is adjustable for windage with the supplied allen wrench as well as for elevation with the use of shims (not included). The included 7 round rectangular magazine is supplied with a finger extension base plate and numbered holes. The under barrel accessory rail shares the dimensions of the MIL-STD-1913 picatinny rail although there is only one locking notch in the forward position.

-One complete Delton upper assembly, Mil-Spec. Has had 300 to 400 rounds through it and has been very well cleaned and taken care of. The upper receiver is forged 7075 T6 aluminum, A3 type flat top. Receiver is hard coat anodized. Bore's surface is coated with dry film lube. Carbine length. The carrier assembly is phosphated 8620 steel with a Carpenter 158 type bolt. Both carrier and bolt are heat treated and plated. Interior of carrier and carrier key are chrome lined. Barrel is 16" made of 4140 steel with a 1x9 twist, manganese phosphated and phosphated under gas block. Has quick sling attachment. 

*Both uppers are 100% complete, ready to snap on a lower and fire.

*Both uppers come with the factory box, manual, and lock.

*I'M LOOKING TO SELL EVERYTHING AS A PACKAGE. I will include:

-TruGlo 4x32 illuminated scope mounted on the Delton upper. Made of a solid piece of aircraft grade aluminum. Has a Mil-Dot reticle. The reticle is illuminated green or red.
-2 new in plastic gen1 Pmags
-2 new in plastic GI anti tilt follower mags 
-60 rds Federal xm193
-50 rounds Winchester FMJ .223
...as seen in picture

$1,000 for everything. That's allotting approximately $600 +/- for M400, $350 + for Delton, $70 +/- for scope. Then the mags and ammo.  

*To the guys making such offers as:  "Will you sell just the Delton upper for $250?" .. the answer is... NO. You couldn't even buy a stripped upper and BCG for $250, much less a complete upper. I understand that it's used, but be realistic. I'm not wasting my time answering dumb offers. By saying X amount is allotted for an item, that's simply justifying the price of the package, THAT IS NOT SAYING THAT IS THE PRICE THAT EACH ITEM IS WORTH IF IT WERE BY ITSELF. If I wanted to go through the pain of selling everything separately, I wouldn't have made this huge detailed add explaining everything as a package deal. I'm selling the whole package exactly as it is listed.


I've always owned guns, just never been familiar with this platform. I had been considering buying an Ar for years, then the scare happened last year and I freaked out not knowing if I would ever be able to get one, so I set out looking to buy anything and everything Ar related. title: For Sale:  SCAM WARNING SCAM WARNING SCAM WARNING
postcontent: Hey armslist community! There is a scam going around that everyone needs to be made aware of. People are sending payments for goods via "certified bank cheque" then they email before the cheque arrives stating that they will have a "mover" to come pick the item up from you. It's usually some excuse of "I'm too busy with work" or some crap. Then they say that there was a mistake and that the money for you and their "mover " was "accidentally" put all on one cheque and they need you to wire transfer the left over money to their "mover". The cheques are FAKE!! A guy was wanting to buy a target from me. The target was only $350.00. The cheque I got in the mail was for $1,980.24! Who the freakin crap pays that much for a $350 item. My bank spotted the cheque as a fake instantly. I know some of you will read this and will have known this for a while. This is for people who are still clueless to this type of scam. If I had cashed the check succuessfully, it would have bounced in a few days and I would owe the money back to the bank! Beware folks, these scumbags are literally everywhere. This all transpired on Craigslist but I figure its only a matter of time before these S.O.B's find out about armslist. Sellers beware! Stay vigilant!

title: For Sale:  Two compete uppers. 1 new 1 used
postcontent:
I'm selling my small collection of Ar15 stuff. I have::

-One complete Sig Sauer M400 Enhanced upper assembly. New in box. The upper receiver is Mil-Spec, machined from 7075-T6 aircraft-grade aluminum forgings and coated with a phosphate hard anodized finish. Carbine length. Has a 16” 1 in 7 inch twist chrome lined and phosphate coated barrel. It uses Sig Sauer's dependable direct-impingement gas operating system that uses a rotating locking bolt. Has Magpul foregrip, A2 front and flip-up rear sights, and a quick detatch sling mount. 

-One complete Delton upper assembly, Mil-Spec. Has had 300 to 400 rounds through it and has been very well cleaned and taken care of. The upper receiver is forged 7075 T6 aluminum, A3 type flat top. Receiver is hard coat anodized. Bore's surface is coated with dry film lube. Carbine length. The carrier assembly is phosphated 8620 steel with a Carpenter 158 type bolt. Both carrier and bolt are heat treated and plated. Interior of carrier and carrier key are chrome lined. Barrel is 16" made of 4140 steel with a 1x9 twist, manganese phosphated and phosphated under gas block. Has quick sling attachment. 

*Both uppers come with the factory box, manual, and lock.

*I'M LOOKING TO SELL EVERYTHING AS A PACKAGE. I will include:

-TruGlo 4x32 illuminated scope mounted on the Delton upper. Made of a solid piece of aircraft grade aluminum. Has a Mil-Dot reticle. The reticle is illuminated green or red.
-2 new in plastic gen1 pmags
-2 new in plastic GI anti tilt follower mags 
-60 rds Federal xm193
-50 rounds Winchester FMJ .223
...as seen in picture


$1,000 for everything. That's allotting $600 +/- for M400, $350 +/- for Delton, $70 +/- for scope. Then the mags and ammo.

**To the guys making such offers as:  "Will you sell just the Delton upper for $250?" .. the answer is... NO. You couldn't even buy a stripped upper and BCG for $250, much less a complete upper. I understand that it's used, but be realistic. I'm not wasting my time answering dumb offers. By saying X amount is allotted for an item, that's simply justifying the price of the package, THAT IS NOT SAYING THAT IS THE PRICE THAT EACH ITEM IS WORTH IF IT WERE BY ITSELF. If I wanted to go through the pain of selling everything separately, I wouldn't have made this huge detailed add explaining everything as a package deal. I'm selling the whole package exactly as it is listed.

I've always owned guns, just never been familiar with this platform. I had been considering buying an Ar for years, then the scare happened last year and I freaked out not knowing if I would ever be able to get one, so I set out looking to buy anything and everything Ar related. I bought all this stuff as a lot from a guy that works with my friend because I work a lot and I don't have time to go wait on stores to open so I can get ammo, mags, and guns. I knew I was probably paying too much, but given the circumstances, I bought this stuff anyways. I bought this lot of exactly as I'm selling it, except for putting approximately 200 rounds through the Delton using a friends lower and throwing in some ammo. I'm in over my head trying to pay for it with accumulating bills and Christmas approaching, so I'm selling in hopes that once I pay everything off, I can buy a complete rifle that I can afford.

title: For Sale:  BNIB!  IWI TAVOR 5.56

postcontent:
IWI US TAVOR® SAR OVERVIEW

The dynamics of the battlefield are forever changing. With the increasing threat of terrorism in our streets to the evolving situations of combat applications, a new paradigm in firearms was required. In 1982, with the foresight of what the modern battlefield was becoming, IWI in a decade long collaboration with the Israel Defense Forces (IDF) R&D developed the new standard issue weapon for the IDF; and the TAVOR® was born. Mr. Zalman Shebs, known as the “father of the TAVOR®,” spearheaded the team to develop a weapon system that was capable of moving from open field conflicts to close-quarter engagements and from daylight to nighttime capabilities – seamlessly on a single mission. In the late 1990’s through the early 2000’s, the TAVOR® underwent unprecedented testing unlike any weapons system anywhere. The TAVOR® began trials with IDF units testing for ergonomics. The TAVOR® then entered the IDF NCO Infantry School for extensive field tests and finally, in 2002, the TAVOR® was given to an army company in the Givati Brigade for real-world testing and use. By September, 2003, the IDF had chosen the TAVOR® rifle as the standard issue for their infantry troops. Today the TAVOR® rifles are in service with IDF Infantry troops and the IDF Special Forces in Israel along with many military and law enforcement agencies in the world.

 IWI and IWI US have brought the same dedication to craft and commitment to performance and reliability to the American customer with the TAVOR® SAR rifle. 

TAVOR® SAR Features Include: ◾ Bullpup configuration allows for short rifle convenience with long rifle accuracy
◾ Optimized ergonomic design for increased comfort and ease-of-use
◾ Clean, long stroke piston operation

◾ Optional 9mm Parabellum conversion kit with CHF barrel, 1:10 twist, CrMoV steel
◾ 100% ambidextrous configuration and operation with optional left-hand bolts for 5.56 NATO and 5.45 x 39mm. No additional parts required to convert to 9mm Parabellum to LH configuration
◾ Integral ambidextrous front and rear quick detachable sling swivel receptacles with push button swivels
◾ Simple field stripping into easily serviceable subassemblies
◾ Mil-Std 100% interchangeability of all TAVOR® SAR parts
◾ Last round stays open on an empty magazine
◾ All metal parts treated for corrosion resistance
◾ Integral rubber recoil pad
